# JetBrains AI Assistant Workflow Guidelines

## Development Workflow
- Use the JetBrains IDEs (IntelliJ IDEA, PyCharm, WebStorm, etc.) for development
- Leverage JetBrains AI Assistant for code generation and suggestions
- Follow the project's branching strategy (typically `main`/`master` for production, `develop` for ongoing work)
- Use feature branches for new functionality

## IDE Configuration
- Ensure JetBrains AI Assistant is properly configured with your Anthropic account
- Configure code style settings to match project standards
- Set up run/debug configurations as appropriate for the project
- Enable relevant inspections and code analyzers

## Code Generation Best Practices
- Use JetBrains AI Assistant for boilerplate code generation
- Review all AI-generated code before committing
- Verify that AI-generated code follows project conventions
- Test AI-generated code thoroughly

## Refactoring with AI
- Utilize AI suggestions for refactoring opportunities
- Verify that refactored code maintains the same functionality
- Update tests as needed after refactoring
- Document significant refactorings in commit messages

## Code Review Process
- Submit pull requests for all changes
- Ensure all tests pass before requesting review
- Include a clear description of the changes
- Address all review comments before merging
- Use AI Assistant to help address feedback when appropriate

## Debugging with AI
- Use AI Assistant to help understand complex code
- Generate debugging strategies for difficult issues
- Create test cases to reproduce bugs
- Document solutions for future reference

## Collaboration
- Share useful AI prompts and techniques with team members
- Establish team-wide AI usage guidelines
- Regularly evaluate and refine AI usage practices
- Maintain awareness of AI limitations and potential biases